subSubSection.paragraph:
Pupa.
Very pale with darker yellow dorsal thorax, anterior wing sheaths and lateral apophyses on abdominal segments V–VIII; comb yellow. Frons with weak warts, cephalothorax weakly rugulose with several rows of dorsal tubercles. Hook row on II with wide medial interruption; with continuous conjunctival spinule band on III and IV. Pedes spurii B weak, vortex weak. Abdomen (
Fig. 3G
) with tergite II with rectangular-shaped armament pattern, quite dense, with anterior transverse band not delimited either by size or density, TIII–V well filled with spinules, TVI with anterior-median elongate/oval area, separated by microspinules median area from posterior transverse band of stronger spinules; TVII and VIII bare. Taeniate setae 3, 4, 4, 5, on VIII evenly distributed along segment. Comb (
Fig. 3L
) with 1 strong posteriorly-directed spine and 2 weaker inner spines. Anal lobe with 20–32 uniserial taeniae.
